  "texts": [
    "Nonetheless, earlier research suggested extensions to TAM by adding variables such as students' attitudes, perceived enjoyment, and perceived credibility.",
    "To determine their compatibility, this study added these variables to TAM.",
    "A person's subjective assessment of and conviction in the effectiveness of deploying particular information technology or work procedures is known as perceived usefulness (Lin et al., 2007).",
    "In this regard, the hypothesis of TAM is grounded upon the idea that perceived usefulness and perceived ease of use have the greatest impact on users' views and plans to use technology (Davis, 1989).",
    "Perceived usefulness is the degree to which a person is confident that the use of certain will enhance their performance (Davis et al., 1989; Davis, 1993)."
  ],
